Got it 👍 — you want **ALL JavaScript concepts (from basic → advanced)** in one clear roadmap. I’ll organize it step-by-step so you can learn like a pro 🚀

---

# 🟢 1. Basics (Foundation)

### ✔ Variables

```js
let a = 10;
const b = 20;
```

### ✔ Data Types

* String, Number, Boolean
* Null, Undefined
* Object, Array

---

### ✔ Operators

```js
+, -, *, /, %, ===, &&, ||
```

---

### ✔ Input / Output

```js
console.log("Hello");
alert("Hi");
```

---

# 🟡 2. Control Flow

### ✔ Conditions

```js
if (age > 18) {
    console.log("Adult");
}
```

### ✔ Switch

```js
switch(day) {
  case 1: console.log("Mon"); break;
}
```

---

### ✔ Loops

```js
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {}
while(condition) {}
```

---

# 🔵 3. Functions

### ✔ Normal Function

```js
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

### ✔ Arrow Function

```js
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
```

### ✔ Callback Function

```js
function greet(name, callback) {
  callback(name);
}
```

---

# 🟣 4. Arrays & Objects

### ✔ Arrays

```js
let arr = [1,2,3];
arr.push(4);
```

### ✔ Array Methods

* map()
* filter()
* reduce()
* forEach()

---

### ✔ Objects

```js
let obj = {name: "Lukhman"};
```

---

# 🟠 5. DOM (Important for Web 🔥)

```js
document.getElementById("id");
document.querySelector(".class");
```

### ✔ Modify HTML

```js
element.innerText = "Hello";
```

---

# 🔴 6. Events

```js
button.onclick = () => {
    alert("Clicked");
}
```

---

# 🟤 7. ES6+ Features (VERY IMPORTANT)

### ✔ Template Literals

```js
`Hello ${name}`
```

### ✔ Destructuring

```js
let {name} = obj;
```

### ✔ Spread Operator

```js
let newArr = [...arr];
```

---

# ⚫ 8. Scope

* Global
* Function
* Block (`let`, `const`)

---

# ⚪ 9. Hoisting

```js
console.log(a);
var a = 5;
```

👉 JS moves declarations to top

---

# 🟢 10. Closures 🔥

```js
function outer() {
  let count = 0;
  return function() {
    count++;
  }
}
```

---

# 🟡 11. this Keyword

* Refers to current object

```js
let obj = {
  name: "Lukhman",
  show() {
    console.log(this.name);
  }
}
```

---

# 🔵 12. Prototypes & Inheritance

```js
function Person(name) {
  this.name = name;
}
Person.prototype.greet = function() {};
```

---

# 🟣 13. Classes (Modern OOP)

```js
class Person {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }
}
```

---

# 🟠 14. Error Handling

```js
try {
  // code
} catch(err) {
  console.log(err);
}
```

---

# 🔴 15. Asynchronous JavaScript 🔥

### ✔ setTimeout

```js
setTimeout(() => {}, 1000);
```

---

### ✔ Promises

```js
let p = new Promise((res, rej) => {
  res("Done");
});
```

---

### ✔ Async/Await

```js
async function getData() {
  let res = await fetch("url");
}
```

---

# 🟤 16. Fetch API (Real-world 🔥)

```js
fetch("api-url")
.then(res => res.json())
.then(data => console.log(data));
```

---

# ⚫ 17. Modules

```js
export default function() {}
import x from './file.js';
```

---

# ⚪ 18. Event Loop (Advanced 🔥)

👉 JS is **single-threaded**
👉 Uses **call stack + queue**

---

# 🟢 19. Memory Management

* Stack (primitive)
* Heap (objects)

---

# 🟡 20. Advanced Topics

* Debouncing & Throttling
* Currying
* Memoization
* Generators
* Web APIs
* Service Workers

---

